commit 8872e39475ea72f8105ce03cdb3dd24153c65c10
Author: Ben Barsdell <bbarsdell@nvidia.com>
Date:   Mon Feb 1 18:28:44 2021 +1100

    Cherry-pick upstream PR 46842

    Use vectorized load/store in GatherOpKernel

    - Vectorized load/store achieves higher memory throughput.
    - This commit chooses the optimal vector size that is compatible with
      the data shape and pointer alignment.
    - Note that the ldg function would require more changes to support the
      vectorized types, but it is not actually needed: the use of 'const
      __restrict__' means the kernel still generates LDG instructions
      without it.
    - Some quick benchmarking showed the following speedups with this commit
      when gathering vectors of length 256 on an NVIDIA TITAN V GPU:
        float64: 1.02x
        float32: 1.07x
        float16: 1.35x
        bool:    1.67x

    Fix alignment_of(T*) to return elements not bytes

    Fix AlignedVector uniform value constructor

    - The old constructor didn't work as expected because Eigen::half has a
      template constructor that accepts anything (which means
      std::is_constructible always returns true) but its implementation can
      still fail for some types.

    Refactor vectorization dispatch in gather kernels

    - This is cleaner and allows other kernels to use DispatchToVectorized
      too in future.

    Address minor review comments from PR 46842

    - Use CHECK_EQ instead of CHECK.
    - Rename template arg T to ValueOrVec to indicate that it may not be
      a primitive type.
    - Add a newline between function definitions.

    Add comments re alignment in gather op kernels
